Describe a skill that was difficult for you to learn
- when you learned it
- why you learned it
- how you learned it
- how you felt when you learned it

I’d like to talk about English speaking, which has been one of the most challenging skills for me to learn.

I first started learning English when I was in grade 6, as it was introduced as a compulsory subject at school. At that time, I wasn’t particularly interested in it because I found it quite difficult and overwhelming. There were so many aspects to focus on, such as grammar, vocabulary, and pronunciation, and I often struggled to form correct sentences or remember new words.

Because of these difficulties, I didn’t perform very well in class and often felt nervous when I had to speak in front of others. As a result, I gradually lost motivation and didn’t invest much time in improving my English during those early years.

However, things began to change when I entered university. I realized how important English was for my future, especially in terms of career opportunities and communication. So, I made a conscious decision to take it more seriously. I enrolled in a language course, practiced regularly by watching English videos, and spent time doing grammar exercises. I also made an effort to speak English every day, even if it was just talking to myself.

Over time, my hard work started to pay off. Although I still make mistakes occasionally, I’ve become much more confident in speaking. I can now express my ideas more clearly and communicate more effectively with others.

Looking back, learning to speak English was definitely a challenging process, but it has also been incredibly rewarding. It has not only improved my communication skills but also boosted my confidence. I believe that with continued effort, I’ll be able to master it in the future.
